@HomeYarp.WebServer_HostAddress = http://localhost:5268

### List applications
GET {{HomeYarp.WebServer_HostAddress}}/api/applications
Accept: application/json

### Create an application (proxies echo.localhost -> postman-echo.com)
POST {{HomeYarp.WebServer_HostAddress}}/api/applications
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "echo",
  "displayName": "Echo Test",
  "description": "Forwards echo.localhost to postman-echo.com",
  "enabled": true,
  "routes": [
    {
      "hosts": ["echo.localhost"],
      "path": "/{**catch-all}"
    }
  ],
  "cluster": {
    "destinations": [
      { "name": "primary", "address": "https://postman-echo.com" }
    ]
  }
}

### Proxy through YARP using the configured host header
GET {{HomeYarp.WebServer_HostAddress}}/get
Host: echo.localhost

### List certificates
GET {{HomeYarp.WebServer_HostAddress}}/api/certificates
Accept: application/json

### Request a certificate from Let's Encrypt (HTTP-01)
# Requires HomeYarp:Acme:Enabled=true, AccountEmail set, and AgreeToTermsOfService=true.
# Inbound port 80 must reach this server's Http listener for any of the listed hostnames.
POST {{HomeYarp.WebServer_HostAddress}}/api/certificates/acme
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "cloud-example",
  "friendlyName": "Cloud (Let's Encrypt)",
  "hostnames": ["cloud.example.com"]
}

### Manually trigger renewal of an ACME-managed certificate
POST {{HomeYarp.WebServer_HostAddress}}/api/certificates/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/renew

### ACME challenge probe (used by Let's Encrypt; should be 404 unless an order is in flight)
GET {{HomeYarp.WebServer_HostAddress}}/.well-known/acme-challenge/probe
